<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3024&amp;p=22327#p22327"><![CDATA[
If you are worried about cost go for <a href="http://www.myropcb.com" class="postlink">myropcb.com</a>.  They will do 1.2mm double layer boards for likely cheaper than normal boards anywhere else.  The production PowerPak and PowerPak Lite boards I have gotten are ~10-15 cents/sqin.  They will also do assembly but sometimes the soldering quality can be questionable...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=228">bunnyboy</a> — Tue Mar 06, 2007 11:03 am</p><hr />
